âœ… What is a .tfvars file?

A .tfvars file is used to assign values to variables defined in variables.tf.

Instead of hardcoding defaults inside the variable block, you define variables and pass values using:

terraform.tfvars


or

something.tfvars


This is very useful for:

Dev

Test

Prod

Different regions

Different instance sizes

ğŸ“Œ Basic Example
1ï¸âƒ£ variables.tf
variable "region" {
  type = string
}

variable "instance_type" {
  type = string
}

variable "instance_count" {
  type = number
}

2ï¸âƒ£ terraform.tfvars
region         = "us-east-1"
instance_type  = "t3.micro"
instance_count = 2

3ï¸âƒ£ main.tf
provider "aws" {
  region = var.region
}

resource "aws_instance" "myec2" {
  ami           = "ami-12345678"
  instance_type = var.instance_type
  count         = var.instance_count
}


Now just run:

terraform plan


Terraform automatically loads terraform.tfvars.
